The paper proposes a new algorithm for reducing the Approximate Nearest Neighbor problem to the Approximate Near Neighbor problem, which is a common problem in computer science and machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of a box split method, which is commonly used in data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
